SUMMARY:From Indiana to AmbassadorŌĆöLessons from a Global Career ( A Glo
 bal Competencies Skills Development Series)
DESCRIPTION:Make your Foreign Service connection explicit.  A two-time U.
 S. Ambassador and Indiana native\, Ambassador Maria Brewer (https://www.s
 tate.gov/biographies/maria-brewer) built her career in the U.S. Foreign S
 ervice\, leading missions in Africa and South Asia and managing complex d
 iplomatic negotiations.  If you are exploring a career in the Foreign Ser
 vice or international policy\, this is a rare opportunity for candid acce
 ss. Hear how assignments are chosen\, how reputations are built\, and how
  leaders navigate pressure overseas.  Come with questions\, leave with cl
 arity about what this path demands and what it offers.Dinner will be prov
 ided.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p data-start="0" data-end="84"><em><strong>
 Make your Foreign Service connection explicit.</strong></em></p><p data-s
 tart="128" data-end="251"><strong data-start="128" data-end="251"><img sr
 c="https://www.state.gov/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Maria-Brewer-photo.jp
 eg" alt="Maria Brewer Photo" loading="lazy"/></strong></p><p data-start="
 253" data-end="451">  A two-time U.S. Ambassador and Indiana native\, Amb
 assador <span style="text-decoration: underline\;"><strong><a href="https
 ://www.state.gov/biographies/maria-brewer">Maria Brewer</a></strong></spa
 n> built her career in the U.S. Foreign Service\, leading missions in Afr
 ica and South Asia and managing complex diplomatic negotiations.</p><p da
 ta-start="453" data-end="680">  If you are exploring a career in the Fore
 ign Service or international policy\, this is a rare opportunity for cand
 id access. Hear how assignments are chosen\, how reputations are built\, 
 and how leaders navigate pressure overseas.</p><p data-start="682" data-e
 nd="775">  Come with questions\, leave with clarity about what this path 
 demands and what it offers.</p><p data-start="682" data-end="775"><strong
  data-start="128" data-end="251">Dinner will be provided.</strong></p>
