SUMMARY:Power Moves ŌĆō Level Up Your Networking Without Freaking Out in 
 International Circles
DESCRIPTION:Step into a live embassy reception simulation with visiting A
 mbassador Maria Brewer (https://www.state.gov/biographies/maria-brewer) a
 nd practice the skills global professionals rely on.&#160\;  In this inte
 ractive session\, you will:      Make formal introductions in a diplomati
 c setting          Navigate hierarchy and cultural protocol          Prac
 tice engaging senior leaders with confidence      Receive direct feedback
  from a former two-time U.S. Ambassador who led missions in Africa and se
 rved in senior roles across the State Department.  Walk away with a clear
 \, repeatable approach to high-level networking you can use at career fai
 rs\, conferences\, and internships this semester.This is a hands-on activ
 ity. Not a lecture.  If you are considering the Foreign Service\, interna
 tional policy\, or any global career\, this is practical training you can
  apply immediately.Snacks will be provided.
