DESCRIPTION:Museum Activities for April First Thursday:4ŌĆō7 p.m. Unwind 
 at the Museum    Live music and crafting celebrating featured exhibit Mul
 yana: Vital Ecosystems. (https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum/event/2123873-dr
 op-in-tours-and-crafting)&#160\;5 p.m. Artist Talk\,Rania Matar: Where Do
  I Go? ┘ä┘ł┘Ŗ┘å ž▒┘łžŁž¤    Catch this special artist talk with photograp
 her Rania Matar\, who will share insights into her creative practice and 
 the powerful portraits. More info and RSVP here. (https://events.iu.edu/e
 vent/2104756-artist-talk-rania-matar-where-do-i-go-) (2nd Floor\, Martin 
 Commons)  5:45 p.m. Special Performance\, Listening to Coral Bones    Exp
 erience a live performance by dancer and performance artist Utam Moses\, 
 who brings Mulyana's work to life while wearing the artist's sculptural c
 oral-inspired costume Form of Silence. The performance begins in the gall
 ery at 5:45 p.m. before moving out toward the Arts Plaza and the First Th
 ursday festival.  Special Giveaway: Tag the museum in a Mulyana: Vitaleco
 systems exhibition photo on social media for a giveaway item while suppli
 es last! (confirm post at giveaway station\, 1st floor atrium)  Newkirk G
 ift Shop Open (2ndFloor Atrium)Know Before You GoThis event is part of th
 e First Thursdays festivals showcase. (https://artsandhumanities.indiana.
 edu/council-programs/first-thursdays/index.html)Read aboutwhere to find u
 s\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>Museum Activities for April First
  Thursday:</strong></p><div id="lw_cal_event_detail_description" class="l
 w_cal_event_detail_block"><p><strong><span data-contrast="none">4ŌĆō7 p.m
 . Unwind at the Museum</span></strong></p><p>    Live music and crafting 
 celebrating featured exhibit <em><a href="https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum
 /event/2123873-drop-in-tours-and-crafting" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
 >Mulyana: Vital Ecosystems.</a>&#160\;</em></p><p aria-level="2"><strong>
 <span data-contrast="none">5 p.m. Artist Talk\,</span><em>Rania Matar: Wh
 ere Do I Go? ┘ä┘ł┘Ŗ┘å ž▒┘łžŁž¤</em></strong></p><p>    Catch this special
  artist talk with photographer Rania Matar\, who will share insights into
  her creative practice and the powerful portraits. <a href="https://event
 s.iu.edu/event/2104756-artist-talk-rania-matar-where-do-i-go-" target="_b
 lank" rel="noopener">More info and RSVP here.</a> (2nd Floor\, Martin Com
 mons)  </p><p class="x_ms-outlook-mobile-reference-message x_skipProofing
 "><strong>5:45 p.m. Special Performance\, <em>Listening to Coral Bones</e
 m></strong></p><p class="x_ms-outlook-mobile-reference-message x_skipProo
 fing">    Experience a live performance by dancer and performance artist 
 Utam Moses\, who brings Mulyana's work to life while wearing the artist's
  sculptural coral-inspired costume <i>Form of Silence</i>. The performanc
 e begins in the gallery at 5:45 p.m. before moving out toward the Arts Pl
 aza and the First Thursday festival.  </p><p class="x_ms-outlook-mobile-r
